M|rules|title: Initialize App Once, Not Per Mount
M|rules|impact: LOW-MEDIUM
M|rules|impactDescription: avoids duplicate init in dev
M|rules|tags: initialization, useEffect, app-startup, side-effects
M|rules|Do not put app-wide initialization that must run once per app load inside `useEffect([])` of a component. Components can remount and effects will re-run. Use a module-level guard or top-level init in 
M|rules|**Incorrect (runs twice in dev, re-runs on remount):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|function Comp() {
M|rules|useEffect(() => {
M|rules|loadFromStorage()
M|rules|checkAuthToken()
M|rules|}, [])
M|rules|// ...
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (once per app load):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|let didInit = false
M|rules|function Comp() {
M|rules|useEffect(() => {
M|rules|if (didInit) return
M|rules|didInit = true
M|rules|loadFromStorage()
M|rules|checkAuthToken()
M|rules|}, [])
M|rules|// ...
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|Reference: [Initializing the application](https://react.dev/learn/you-might-not-need-an-effect#initializing-the-application)